Project Idea: Recipe Manager

Project overview:  
The purpose of the Recipe Manager is to provide an easy way to keep track of different recipes in one place. Instead of storing recipes in random notes or paper lists, users will have a clean interface to create, view, edit, and delete recipe entries. I will create a CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) web application built using NodeJS, ExpressJS, MongoDB (Mongoose), and EJS templates.

The goal of this application is to allow users to store and manage their favorite recipes in an organized online directory. Users will be able to add new recipes, view existing ones, update details, and delete recipes they no longer want. The mongoose model will follow with name, ingredients, instructions, and createdAt. The user will be able to navigate to the recipe list page and from there the user can add a recipe, edit a recipe, and delete a recipe. Also clicking delete will show a confirmation message.
